description*.en: "Static Pressure" is the pressure at a nominated point in a fluid. Every point in a steadily flowing fluid, regardless of the fluid speed at that point, has its own static pressure $P$, dynamic pressure $q$, and total pressure $P_0$. The total pressure is the sum of the dynamic and static pressures, that is $P_0 = P + q$.
